**Returns**

- \`druid.button\` — The current button instance

</div>

### \`druid.button.is_enabled(): boolean\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Get button enabled state.
By default all Buttons are enabled on creating.

**Returns**

- \`boolean\` — True, if button is enabled now, False otherwise

</div>

### \`druid.button.set_click_zone(zone: node|string|nil): druid.button\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Set additional button click area.
Useful to restrict click outside of stencil node or scrollable content.
If button node placed inside stencil node, it will be automatically set to this stencil node.

**Parameters**

- \`zone\`: \`node|string|nil\` — Gui node

**Returns**

- \`druid.button\` — The current button instance

</div>

### \`druid.button.set_key_trigger(key: hash|string): druid.button\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

Set key name to trigger this button by keyboard.

**Parameters**

- \`key\`: \`hash|string\` — The action_id of the input key. Example: "key_space"

**Returns**

- \`druid.button\` — The current button instance

</div>

### \`druid.button.get_key_trigger(): hash\`

<div class="api-symbol-body">

